						               													<description>Objective: be the first leading all (3) of your meeples home&amp;#10; - moving by turns -&amp;#10;a 'Pachisi'-variant&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has a set of 3 meeples that start in his/her corner of the board. The goal is to move the meeples around the board back to the &amp;quot;home&amp;quot; section (=start). Movement is controlled by dice. All players move around the same board, so they may throw out others meeples. Thrown ones are returned to their player's corner and must start again. The winner is the first player to move all meeples &amp;quot;home&amp;quot;. &amp;#10;The major difference is located as red square (8 spaces) in the middle of the board, which must passed 4 times. It becomes a bottleneck, because only one meeple may move into (next step out of) it. During this period it can be thrown out easily.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
